{{ infobox nobility | name = Adelaide of Guelders | image = | caption = | noble family = House of Wassenberg | father = [[Otto I, Count of Guelders]] | mother = [[Richardis of Bavaria]] | spouse = [[William I, Count of Holland]] | issue = {{plainlist| *[[Floris IV, Count of Holland|Floris IV]] * [[Otto III van Holland|Otto]] * William * Richarda * Ada }} | birth_date = {{circa|1182}} | birth_place = | death_date = 1218 | death_place = | burial_place = [[Rijnsburg Abbey]] }} '''Adelaide of Guelders''' ({{circa|1182}} &ndash; 1218) was the daughter of Count [[Otto I, Count of Guelders|Otto I]] of Guelders and his wife, [[Richardis of Bavaria|Richardis]], the daughter of Duke [[Otto I of Wittelsbach, Duke of Bavaria|Otto I]] of Bavaria and [[Agnes of Loon]]. Also known as Adelaide of Bellich or Alice of Guelders.
In 1197 in [[Stavoren]], she married Count [[William I, Count of Holland|William I]] of Holland. They had five children: # [[Floris IV, Count of Holland|Floris IV]] (24 June 1210 in [[The Hague]]&ndash;19 July 1234 in [[Corbie]], [[France]]), succeeded his father as [[Count of Holland]] # [[Otto III van Holland|Otto]] (d. 1249), Regent of Holland in 1238–1239, [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Utrecht|Bishop of Utrecht]] # William (d. 1238), Regent of Holland in 1234–1238. # Richarda (d. 1262) # Ada (d. 1258), Abbess at [[Rijnsburg]] from 1239 until her death
Adelaide died in 1218, while her husband was away on the [[Fifth Crusade]]. She was buried in [[Rijnsburg Abbey]].
