'''Comfort Annor''' (1949 – 22 February 2015) was a [[Ghana]]ian musician known for her soothing unique voice, alternating between a [[mezzo-soprano]] and a [[contralto]] in the 90s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/showbiz/news/201502/232840.php|title=Veteran Gospel Musician Comfort Annor Cries For Help!...Kidney And Liver Almost Gone|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/entertainment/2015/february-22nd/veteran-gospel-musician-comfort-annor-is-dead.php|title=Ghana News - Veteran gospel musician Comfort Annor has died|last=Myjoyonline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref>
==Biography==
Comfort Annor also known as Ama Otu Bea was a Deaconess of The Church of Pentecost and hails from [[Kasoa Bawjiase]] in the [[Central Region (Ghana)|Central Region]] of [[Ghana]]. Madam Comfort had seven children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/showbiz/news/201504/238039.php|title=Comfort Annor To Be Buried On May 30|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref>
She died on 22 February 2015 at the [[Komfo Anokye Teaching Hospital|Okomfo Anokye]] aged 66.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghana-news.adomonline.com/entertainment/2015/february-22nd/veteran-musician-comfort-annor-is-dead.php|title=Ghana News - Veteran musician Comfort Annor is dead|last=adomonline.com|website=www.ghana-news.adomonline.com|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://enewsgh.com/2015/02/22/obituary-gospel-musician-comfort-annor-dead/|title=OBITUARY: Gospel musician Comfort Annor DEAD{{!}} ENewsGh|date=2015-02-22|website=Proudly Ghanaian! {{!}} ENewsGh|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.peacefmonline.com/pages/showbiz/news/201504/238039.php|title=Comfort Annor To Be Buried On May 30|last=Online|first=Peace FM|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref> Although the cause of her death is not known, it is purported that she had been battling with liver and kidney ailment since October 2014 when she was taken ill.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.africanseer.com/news/400120-ghanaian-gospel-musician-comfort-annor-has-died.html|title=Ghanaian Gospel Musician Comfort Annor Has Died|website=AfricanSeer.com|access-date=2016-08-08}}</ref>
==Songs== Madam Comfort is popularly known for her hit songs "Asaase Dahɔ Gyan", "W’awo Me ɔba", "Abraham Sarah", "Mewo Agyapadeɛ", "Hena Na W’aye".<ref>{{cite web|title=Gospel musician Comfort Annor has died|url=http://www.graphic.com.gh/entertainment/music/gospel-musician-comfort-annor-has-died.html|website=Graphic.com|publisher=Ghraphic online|accessdate=8 August 2016}}</ref> However, her major Album is "Dom Hene", which was released in 2006 and has about 10 songs.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dom Hene|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/dom-hene/id367823393|website=Itunes|publisher=Itunes|accessdate=8 August 2016}}</ref>
