{{ref-improve|date=April 2018}} '''Merena''' was a military officer of the [[Sassanid Empire]] during the reign of [[Shapur II]] in the 4th century. He was a cavalry commander in the [[Sassanid army]] in the course of the [[Roman-Persian Wars]] soon after the [[Battle of Ctesiphon (363)|Battle of Ctesiphon]] in 363, which took place outside the Sassanid capital [[Ctesiphon]] in what is now [[Iraq]]. As cavalry commander, he also appeared in the [[Battle of Maranga]]<ref>Ammianus Marcellinus, ''Res Gestae'', Book 25, [http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/25*.html#1.1 1.10]</ref>.
He was among those killed at the subsequent [[Battle of Samarra]], a few hours before the death of the Roman emperor [[Julian the Apostate|Julian]]<ref>Ammianus Marcellinus, ''Res Gestae'', Book 25, [http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/25*.html#1.1 3.13]</ref>.
