The '''murder of Hilda Feste''' was a [[criminal case]] in [[Norway]], involving the [[rape]] and [[murder]] of a 98-year-old victim, '''Hilda Feste''' (20 February 1913 – 1 January 2012),<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2012/11/09/magasinet/hilda_feste/os-drapet/innenriks/drap/24282553/ |title=Hilda Feste var snart 99 år da hun åpnet døra for en ukjent mann 1. nyttårsdag - magasinet |publisher=Dagbladet.no |date=1913-02-20 |accessdate=2013-09-21}}</ref> perpetrated by then 19-year-old '''Christian Haugland''' (born 1993). In December 2012, Haugland was found guilty of the crime and sentenced to 19 years in prison, and he accepted the sentence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nettavisen.no/nyheter/article3531154.ece |title=HILDA FESTE - Christian Haugland (19) godtar dommen |publisher=Nettavisen.no |date= |accessdate=2013-09-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2012/12/13/nyheter/drap/voldtekt/rettsak/anke/24810839/ |title=Drapsdømt velger studier framfor ankebehandling - nyheter |publisher=Dagbladet.no |date=2012-12-13 |accessdate=2013-09-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ba.no/nyheter/article6393195.ece |title=Christian Haugland godtar dommen |language=nb |publisher=ba.no |date=2012-12-13 |accessdate=2013-09-21}}</ref> The case attracted media attention due to its brutality. The verdict described the crime as one of the most serious crimes ever committed in Norway by such a young man.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vg.no/nyheter/innenriks/artikkel.php?artid=10056436 |title=19 års fengsel for drapet på Hilda Feste - VG Nett om Os-drapet |publisher=Vg.no |date= |accessdate=2013-09-21}}</ref>
